src: tɕe mtsʰu nɯ ɲɤ-me tɕe,
trs: Then the lake disappeared.' (2003nyima-2, 106)

src: ɯ-ftsoʁ nɯ ɲo-me, ɲo-nɯ-ɣɤ-me qʰe
trs: Her female hybrid yak was gone, she lost it.' (gesar 2003, 35)

src: tʂu ɯ-rkɯ zɯ si tɯ-pʰɯ pjɤ-tu,  si tɯ-pʰɯ nɯ ɯ-pʰaʁ ɯ-ntsi nɯ pjɤ-rom ʑo, ɯ-pʰaʁ ɯ-ntsi nɯ pjɤ-k-ɤrŋi-ci ʑo,
trs: On the side of the road, there was a tree, one half of that tree was dry and the other half was green. (The divination2002, 11-12)

src: tɕoχtsi ɯ-taʁ nɯtɕu, nɤkinɯ, qajɣi kɯβde, cʰa kɯβde-phoŋ pjɤ-k-ɤ-ta-ci.
trs: On the table, there were four pieces of bread and four bottles of alcohol.' (140510 sanpian sheye-zh, 51)

src: alo nɤ alo kɤ-ɣe-a ma ɯ-ʁɤri ku-kɯ-ɣi tɕe, ɲɯ-ɣɯtsʰɤdɯɣ.
trs: I came (here, eastwards from the point of origin) by (the road that lies) closer to the mountain, when one comes by the (road that is located) in the front, it is too hot.' (conversation, 140510)

src: tɕe ndzom ɯ-pa nɯtɕu tɯ-ci ɯ-rkɯ nɯtɕu pɣɤtɕɯ nɯ to-nɯ-ɬoʁ tɕe
trs: The bird came out from under the bridge, near the river.' (2002 qaCpa, 191)

src: tɯmɯnɤmkʰa zɯ pjɤ-nɯ-ɬoʁ-nɯ.
trs: (They) came down from heaven.' (150828 niulang-zh, 48)

src: sɲikuku ʑo tɕe tɯmɯnɤmkʰa nɯtɕu, qro χsɯm pjɯ-ɣi-nɯ
trs: Everyday, three pigeons came down from heaven.' (31-deluge, 47)

src: <bazi> ɯ-ŋgɯ ri tɤ-ŋke-a ma, kɯ-ɤrqʰi kɤ-ɕe mɯ-ku-cʰa-a.
trs: I had a walk in the yard, I cannot go very far.' (conversation, 2017-09-21)

src: rɟɤmtsʰu ɯ-pɕoʁ tɕe jo-ndʑaʁ tɕe jo-ɕe.
trs: He swam towards the sea.' (150830 baihe jiemei-zh, 212)

src: rɟara ɯ-ŋgɯ cʰɤ-rɟɯɣ ri,
trs: He ran out into the yard.' (140505 bulaimei-zh,106)

src: zgo tʰɤstɯɣ ja-nnɯ-pɣaʁ-ndʑi, tɯ-ci tɕʰi jarma ja-n-nɯmɢla-ndʑi mɤ-xsi ma,
trs: It is not known how many mountains and rivers they crossed.'  (qajdoskAt 2002, 50)

src: ji-kʰɯtsa sɤ-rku tsʰaŋ nɯnɯ, ta-nɤjoʁjoʁ-nɯ ta-nɯtʰaj-nɯ qʰe rcanɯ, <xuexiao> ɣɯ ɯ-<caochang> ɯ-χcɤl ʑo na-tsɯm-nɯ.
trs: They lifted up the cupboard where we put our bowls, and carried it to the center of the school's playground.' (150831 BZW kAnArRaR, 22)

src: ɯ-pɕi zɯ jú-wɣ-sco, sɤtɕʰa kɯ-ɤrqʰi zɯ pjɯ́-wɣ-lɤt ma-pɯ́-wɣ-sat ra tu-kɯ-ti ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: One has to send (the snake) outside, to a place far away without killing it, people say.'  (2010-11, 11)

src: ɯ-wa kɯ ɣɯ-lɤ́-wɣ-lɤt-i
trs: His father give us a ride here (from Chengdu to Mbarkham).' (elicited)

src: rŋɯl rɟɤskɤt ɯ-taʁ tɤ́-wɣ-sɯx-ɕe ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: They made her go up the silver stairs.' (2003 Kunbzang, 251)

src: ɲɤ-mtsɯr qʰe tɕendɤre ɯ-pʰɯŋgɯ nɯtɕu iɕqʰa nɯ, qajɣi ci ɲɤ-tɕɤt tɕe to-nɯ-ndza.
trs: He became hungry, took a piece of bread from the folds of his clothes and ate it.' (150830 san ge heshang-zh, 139)

src: rɟɤmtsʰu ɯ-mŋu zɯ ju-tɕɤt-nɯ tɕe
trs: (The whalers) take (the whale) to the shore of the ocean.' (160703 jingyu, 35)

src: aʑo tʰɤjtɕu jamar nɤ-kʰa ju-ɣi-a pe?
trs: At what time should I go to your house?' (elicited)

src: a-rca jɤ-ɣi
trs: Come with me.' (several attestations)

src: nɤ-rca tu-ɣi-a ra ma kutɕu aʑo-sti ku-rɤʑi-a mɯ́j-cʰa-a
trs: I am going (to heaven) with you, I cannot stay here alone.' (02-deluge, 79)

src: nɤ-rca tu-kɯ-tsɯm-a ra
trs: Take me with you (to heaven).' (02-deluge, 70)

src: tɕe tɕekɯ zɯ rŋɯl-kʰri ndi ɲɤ-ɕtʰɯz, tɕendi zɯ kɯ ko-ɕtʰɯz tɕe,
trs: In the east side, he turned the silver seat towards the west, and in the west side he turned (the other seat) towards the east.' (smAnmi2003, 157)

src: kɯ-fsoʁ ɯ-jroʁ kɯ-fse ci ju-tʰi tɕe,
trs: The shooting star leaves something like a bright trail.' (29-mWBZi, 92)

src: jɤ-armbat tɕe ku-rtoʁ tɕe, tɕeri ɯʑo ɯ-pi ʁnɯz nɯni pjɤ-ŋu-ndʑi.
trs: As he moved closer, he saw that (the people about to be executed) were his brothers.' (140507 jinniao-zh, 334)

src: mɯ-jɤ-ɲat ʑo mɤɕtʂa jo-ɕe
trs: He went (after them) until he became tired.' (160706 poucet6, 45)

src: tɕʰi nɯ ɣɯ ɯ-taʁ tɤ-ari ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: He went up the tree trunk stairway.' (2005 Kunbzang, 65)

src: pot stʰɯci kɯ-ɤrqʰi me ri, nɯtɕu tɤ-ari ɕti tɕe
trs: There is no (place) further away (from here) than Tibet, but he went there.' (meimeidegushi, 32)

src: rɟa pjɤ-ɕe tɕe
trs: He went to China.' (Gesar, 219)

src: ``rqaco pjɯ-ɕe-a" tu-kɯ-ti, ``smɯlju pɯ-ari-a" tu-ti-nɯ. tɕe ma nɯnɯ zgo nɯ tu-kɯ-ɕe tɕe, akɯ tɕe pa pjɯ-kɯ-ɕe ɲɯ-ra loβ, tɕe núndʐa ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: People say `I will go (down) to Rqakyo', or `I went (down) to Smeliu', this is because one has to go up a mountain and go down on the east side.' (150904 akW andi-zh, 16)

src: alo ji-tɯ-ci cʰɯ-kɯ-ɣi, <jiaomujiao> tɯ-ci nɯ
trs: Our river upstream (in Kamnyu), the Kyomkyo river...' (150820 ZNGWloR, 11)

src: kɯki tɯ-ci cʰɯ-kɯ-ɣi kɯki tú-wɣ-nɯɴqʰu lu-kɯ-ɕe tɕe,
trs: (If) you follow this creek upstream...' (04-cuiniao-zh, 65)

src: tɕʰipʰɯɣ ɯ-pɕoʁ lu-kɯ-ɕe nɯ tɕe ``lo", tɕʰimtʰa ɯ-pɕoʁ cʰɯ-kɯ-ɕe nɯ tɕe ``tʰɯ-ari-a",  ``tʰi'' tú-wɣ-nɯ-sɤrmi ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: One calls going towards the source of the river \textsc{upstream}, and going towards the lower reaches of the river `downstream.' (150904 akW andi, 24-25)

src: tsʰuβdɯn kɯ-sɤ-sɯxɕɤt lɤ-ari-a.
trs: I went to Tshobdun to teach.' (150819 kumpGa, 78)

src: rɟa sɤz kɯ-ɤrqʰi me ri, nɯtɕu tʰɯ-ari ɕti
trs: There is no (place) further away (from here) than China, but he went there.' (meimeidegushi, 40)

src: tɕɯχtsi kɤ-ari-j, kɯ-nɤmɲo
trs: We went to Cogtse, to visit.' (conversation, 2013-10-15)

src: jɤɣɤt ci cʰɯ-ɕe-a
trs: I am going to the toilets.' (heard several times in context)

src: kɤmɲɯ mɯ-lɤ-tsɯm-a
trs: I did not take  (my mobile phone) to Kamnyu.' (said after having come back to Mbarkham, conversation, 16-02-21)

src: tɕe mbarkʰom kɯ-rɤ-βzjoz tʰɯ-ɣe-a,
trs: I came to Mbarkham to study.' (140501 tshering skyid, 48)

src: ɕlaʁ ʑo tɯ-ci ɯ-ŋgɯ cʰɤ-mtsʰaʁ tɕe pjɤ-ʑɣɤ-sat.
trs: He immediately jumped into the water and committed suicide.' (qajdoskAt 2002, 117)

src: <wugui> nɯ tɯ-ci ɯ-ŋgɯ lo-nɯ-ɬoʁ
trs: The turtle came out of the water.' (elicited, based on a text example)

src: tɯrmɯkʰa ri tɕe tɕendi ri tɤŋe ɯ-sɤ-ɕqʰlɤt pɕoʁ ri tu.
trs: (This star) is found at dusk in the west, at the place where the sun sets.' (29-mWBZi,76)

src: tɯ-rdoʁ nɯnɯ, ɕɤrpɕoʁ ko-ɕe, tɯ-rdoʁ nɯnɯ ʁmbɣi ɯ-sɤ-ɕqʰlɤt nɯtɕu ɲɤ-ɕqʰlɤt.
trs: One (of the feathers) went to the east, another one disappeared in the direction where the sun sets.' (140510 sanpian yumao-zh, 17-18)

src: tɤŋe ɲɤ-nɯ-ɬoʁ
trs: The sun rose (from the east, towards the west)'. (elicited)

src: iʑora tɕe ``sɤrndzu kɤ-ari-a" tu-kɯ-ti ŋu.
trs: We (in Kamnyu) say ``I went (eastwards) to Sarndzu.' (150904 akW andi, 21)

src: <jinchuan> nɯ-azɣɯt-i ri
trs: When we arrived in Jinchuan...' (2010-1, 3)

src: ɯʑo kɯ (<dianhua>) ku-lɤt ɕti ma, aʑo ɲɯ-lat-a mɤ-kʰɯ tɕe, andi ku-rɤʑi tɕe ɯ-<dianhuahaoma> a-kɤ-ti mɤ-kʰɯ
trs: It is he who calls (me on the phone), I cannot call him, he lives in the west (in France), I cannot say his phone number.' (conversation, 16-12-28)

src: andi smɤnmimitoʁkuɕana ɕɯ-nɤʁdan-a ra tɕe, ɲɯ-ɕe-a tɕe, kɤ-ɣe-a tɕe a-pɯ-ŋu
trs: I am going to the west to invite Smanmi Metog Koshana (to our realm), let us do (the wedding) when I come (back).' (smAnmi 2003, 36)

src: nɯ rɟɤkɤr ɲɯ-ɕe kɯ-ra,
trs: That (daughter) has to go to India.' (Gesar, 13)

src: nɯ χwɤr ku-ɕe kɯ-ra ɕti,
trs: That (daughter) has to go to Hor.' (Gesar, 12)

src: qapri nɯ kɯ kɯ-cʰu pʰɤri li kɤ́-wɣ-tɕɤt ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: The snake took him to the opposite bank.' (divination 2005, 50)

src: kɯ-cʰu pʰɤri nɯtɕu ɯ-wa ko-tsɯm tɕe,
trs: He took his father to the opposite bank of the river.' (2011-05-nyima, 43)

src: nɯ-<beifen> kɯ-mbro nɯra lu-maŋlo-nɯ,
trs: The elders (sit) higher (upstream).' (31-khAjmu, 61)

src: tɕe nɯnɯ tɤ-ftsa nɯ tɤ-rpɯ sɤz lu-kɯ-maŋlo mɯ-pjɤ-ŋgrɤl
trs: Nephews could not be seated higher (upstream) than their maternal uncles.' (08-saCW, 12)

src: nɤʑo ɲɯ-tɯ-maŋlo ɕti ma aʑo ɲɯ-maŋtʰi-a ɕti tɕe,
trs: You are upstream and I am downstream.' (2014, lang he yang-zh, 20-211)

src: nɯ ɯ-pa pɯ-ari tɕe tɕe, a-wɤmɯ ɯ-ɣe pɯ-nɯ-ŋu, a-sqʰaj ɣɯ ɯ-ɣe pɯ-nɯ-ŋu tɕe aʑo tɤrcɯrca ``a-ɣe" tu-ti-a ɕti.
trs: In the (generation) below (that of one's nephews), I say \forme{a-ɣe} `my grandchild' (to all grandnephews), whether they are my brother's grandchildren or my sister's granchildren.' (140425 kWmdza02, 16)

src: tɕe ɯ-tɯ-sɤ-scit kɯ nɯ tɤ-rʑaʁ nɯ-ari mɯ-pjɤ-tso.
trs: It was so nice there that he did not realize that (a lot of) time had passed.' (28-smAnmi, 290)

src: kɤntɕʰɯ-sla ɲɤ-ɕqʰlɤt ri
trs: Several months passed.' (140513 mutong de disheng-zh, 13)

src: χsɯ-xpa jɤ-tsu-j,
trs: We have been (together) for three years (now), and ...' (Norbzang 2005, 59)

src: praʁkʰaŋ ɯ-ŋgɯ nɯtɕu lo-ɕe ɲɯ-ŋu tɕeri
trs: He went into the cave.' (140425 shizi huli he lu-zh, 47)

src: kʰa ɯ-ŋgɯ lɤ-ɣi-ndʑi tɕe,
trs: Come inside the house.' (140507 tangguowu-zh, 90)

src: spjaŋkɯ nɯ kɯ kɯm lo-stʰoʁ tɕe, ɯ-ŋgɯ lo-ɕe.
trs: The wolf pushed the door and went in.' (140428 xiaohongmao-zh, 80)

src: kʰa ɯ-pɕi cʰɤ-ɬoʁ.
trs: She came out of the house.' (140428 xiaohongmao-zh, 28)

src: ɕɤmɯɣdɯ ɯ-lɤcu ɯ-mŋu ri qandʑi cʰɯ-rku-nɯ
trs: The load the bullet into the (trunk) of the musket from the opening (the muzzle)' (28-CAmWGdW, 38)

src: nɯnɯ mɯzi nɯ tu-nɯt tɕe tɕe qandʑi nɯ lu-βde tɕe ju-ɕe ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: The gunpowder flares and drives the bullet out (of the trunk of the muzzle).' (28-CAmWGdW, 85-86)

src: scapa lo-χɕoʁ
trs: He unsheathed his sword.' (140514 huishuohua de niao-zh, 178)

src: <suoluomen> nɯ kɯ aʑo kɯki pʰoŋ ɯ-ŋgɯ tɕe tʰɯ́-wɣ-rku-a ŋu,
trs: Solomon put me in this bottle.' (140512 yufu yu mogui-zh, 78)

src: mar-rgɤm ɯ-ŋgɯ zɯ χwɤr ra ɣɯ nɯ-rɟɤβlun thamtɕɤt ɣɯ nɯ-ku nɯ pjɤ-rku
trs: He had put the heads of all the ministers of Hor in a butter box.' (gesar, 373)

src: ɯ-sloχpɯn nɯ kɯ rgɤm ɯ-ŋgɯ zɯ, nɤkinɯ, χɕɤlmdoŋ ci to-tɕɤt tɕe ɲɤ-mbi
trs: His teacher took a spyglass from a box and gave it to him.' (140508 benling gaoqiang de si xiongdi-zh, 73)

src: taqaβ nɯ ɯ-rna ri spoʁ tɕe, tɕe nɯtɕu tɤ-ri ɲɯ́-wɣ-rʁe,
trs: The needle has a hole at the (needle's) eye$_i$, and one passes the thread though it$_i$.' (12-kAtsxWb, 33-34)

src: nɯŋa ɯ-ndʐi tʰɯ-kɤ-rɤɣdɯt ɯ-ŋgɯ nɯtɕu ko-ɕe.
trs: He went into the distended hide of the cow.' (31-deluge, 25)

src: nɯ ɣɯ ɯ-rna ɯ-ŋgɯ xɕelwi ko-ɕe ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: A tick went into his ear.' (kAndZislama 2003, 115)

src: tɯ-ɕa ɯ-ŋgɯ kɤ-ari qʰe, koŋla ɯ-ŋgɯ ʑo ku-ɕe ɕti.
trs: When (its thorn) goes into the flesh, it penetrates completely.' (17-xCAj, 69)

src: tɕe ɯ-rme nɯ ɯ-pɕi ɲɤ-ɕtʰɯz, ɯ-ndʐi nɯ ɯ-ŋgɯ ko-ɕtʰɯz tɕe tɕe to-ŋga.
trs: He turned the fur (of the jacket)$_i$ towards the outside, and the leather towards the inside and wore it$_i$.' (140513 mutong de disheng-zh, 55)

src: pjɤ-ɣɤrɤt tɕe ɯ-rɟit ra kɯ ko-rɤɕi-nɯ ɲɤ-rɤɕi-nɯ ʑo ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: She threw them$_i$ down (there), and her children tore them$_i$  apart (pulled them$_i$  right and left in a disorderly way).' (2012 Norbzang, 401)

src: lɯlu nɯ kɯ ci ko-mɟa, ci ɲo-mɟa tɕe
trs: The cat grabbed one on his left and one on his right.' (lWlu 2002, 78)

src: tɤ-tɕɯ nɯ pɯ-nɯ-xtɕi-nɯ pɯ-nɯ-wxti-nɯ tɕe kʰɤɕkʰɤr tɕu ku-ɕe-nɯ.
trs: Men, whether they are young or older, go to the men's \textsc{eastwards} seating place.' (31-khAjmu, 30)

src: saŋdi nɯtɕu si ɲɯ-ta-nɯ
trs: They put the firewood on the \textsc{westwards} seating place (that is opposite the men's \textsc{eastwards} seating place).' (31-khAjmu, 36)

src: ɯ-sqar nɯ tʰɯ-ari tɕe tɕe, nɤki, kɯki tú-wɣ-stu tɕe cʰɯ́-wɣ-ɣnda.
trs: As the intersection of the (upper and lower) warp threads goes down, one does like that to tamp it down.' (vid-20140429090403, 62)

src: ɯ-taʁ cʰo ɯ-pa ɣɯ ɯ-ʁjar ni pjɯ-ɤqɤtʂʰa-ndʑi, nɯtɕu tɯ-jlɤβ ɲɯ́-wɣ-rʁe tɕe
trs: The upper and lower warp threads are crossed, and at (the crossing place) one inserts the weft.' (additional explanation provided while transcribing the video from which \figref{fig:loom1} is taken).%vid-20140429090403

src: ɕnat kɯ tɤ-ri ra tɕe nɯ kɯ tú-wɣ-sɯ-joʁ tɕe,
trs: One lifts the (warp) threads with the heddles.' (2011-06-thaXtsa)

src: qartsɯ tɕe ku-cɯ ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: In winter, (the bear) hibernates.' (21-pri, 51)

src: si ɯ-ngɯ tɤ-kɯ-so, ɯ-ŋgɯ tɤ-kɯ-rom, nɯnɯ pjɯ-saχsi tɕe, nɯ ɯ-ŋgɯ ɕ-tu-cɯ ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: Trees whose inside is hollow, whose inside is dried, (the bear) (hollows) it completely, goes up (the hole) and hibernates (there).' (21-pri, 55)

src: mɯŋi ɲɯ-sɤx-ɕe tʂu nɯnɯre ri,
trs: On the road (from Kamnyu) towards Mengi...' (140522 Kamnyu zgo, 2)

imt: east side \textsc{dem}  \textsc{topo} be:\textsc{fact} west side  \textsc{topo} be:\textsc{fact}
src: akɯ pɕoʁ nɯ mɯŋi ŋu, andi pɕoʁ praʁwɯ ŋu.
trs: Mengi is on the east, and Praqwu (a small locality in Kamnyu) is on the west.' (140522 Kamnyu zgo, 21)

src: tɕeri qandʐe kɯ tʰɤlwa ʁɟa cʰɯ-ndze ɲɯ-ɕti.
trs: The earthworm only eats earth.' (25-akWzgumba, 126)

src: ɯ-rkɯ kɯ-fse ku-ʑe tɕe, mɯ-kɤ-arɕo mɤɕtʂa ku-ndze ɣɤʑu,
trs: Sometimes (the eclipse) starts on one side, and `eats' (the moon) until it (disappears) completely.' (29-mWBZi, 155)

src: nɯŋa qʰe qaʑo tsʰɤt nɯra pjɤ-dɤn-nɯ tɕe, nɯtɕu ɲɯ-nɯrɯ-nɯ tɕe sɯjno tu-ndza-nɯ pjɤ-ŋu,
trs: There were many cows, sheep and goats, and they were eating grass there.' (150819 woniu-zh, 9)

src: tɯ-ci ko-nɯkʰɯɣ ʑo ko-tsʰi.
trs: He gulped the water.' (140429 jiedi-zh, 70)

src: tɯ-ci kɯnɤ cʰɯ-ɕe mɯ-ɲɤ-kʰɯ. tɯ-ci cʰɯ-tsʰi mɯ-ɲɤ-kʰɯ
trs: Even water could not go (down his throat), he could not drink anymore.' (of a person suffering from throat cancer, 27-tWfCAl, 81)

src: ɯ-wa nɯ kɯ cʰa ntsɯ cʰɯ-tsʰi qʰe, ɯ-me mɯ́j-nɯβdaʁ
trs: Her father was drinking alcohol all the time, and did not take care of his daughter.' (17-lhazgron, 68)

src: ɯ-sŋɯro lu-χɤβ ʑo tɕe nɯ βɣɤza nɯ ɯ-kɯr ɯ-ŋgɯ lu-nɯ-ɕe ɕti
trs: (The frog)$_i$ draws its$_i$ breath and the fly goes by itself into its$_i$ mouth.' (27-qaCpa, 7)

src: ki ɯ-ʁɤri sɯstaʁ ʑo ɯ-ɕɣa a-nɯ-xtɕi ra
trs: May she become younger than before!' (Norbzang 2005, 251)

src: mɤʑɯ ʑo ɯ-kʰa ra to-wxti tɕe,
trs: His house had become even bigger.' (140430 yufu he tade qizi-zh, 222)

src: tɕeri ɯ-tɕɯ nɯ ʑɯrɯʑɤri cʰɤ-wxti
trs: His son progressively grew up.' (28-smAnmi, 10)

src: tɕe <yimi> jamar ma tu-rɲɟi mɤ-cʰa ma
trs: It cannot grow longer than about one meter.' (11-qarGW, 114)

imt: fir \textsc{gen}  \textsc{3sg}.\textsc{poss}-fruit \textsc{ipfv}:\textsc{upstream}-be.long a.little be:\textsc{fact} \textsc{lnk} \textsc{filler} maize cob a.little be.like:\textsc{fact}
src: tɯrgi ɣɯ ɯ-mat lu-rɲɟi tsa ŋu tɕe, nɤki jima popo tsa fse.
trs: The fir cone is elongated, a bit like the corncob (07-tAtho, 32)

src: ɕɤr nɯ cʰɯ-rɲɟi, sŋi nɯ cʰɯ-xtɯt ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: The nights are becoming longer, and the days shorter.' (elicited)

src: pɯ-kɯ-xtɕi tɕe, nɯnɯ ʑŋgri nɯ nɯ-mɤrʑaβ ɯ-raŋ tɕe, tɯ-kɤrme cʰɯ́-wɣ-rɤɕi tɕe, cʰɯ-rɲɟi ŋu to-ti-nɯ tɕe,
trs: When we were young, people said that when there is a shooting star, if you pull your hair, it will grow longer.' (29-mWBZi, 102)

src: ɕɤɣ nɯ li kɯ-mbɯ\redp{}mbro tu-βze cʰa
trs: The juniper grows very high.' (08-CAG, 1)

src: tɯrgi laŋlaŋ nɯnɯ, la-βzu ɕimɯma nɯ ɲɯ-ɤrŋi,
trs: The fir cone is green when it has just grown out.' (08-tWrgi, 72)

src: ɯ-ru ra kɯ-xtsʰɯ\redp{}xtsʰɯm ŋu ri, kɯ-zɯ\redp{}zri ʑo cʰɯ-βze qʰe,
trs: Although its stalk is very thin, it grows very long.' (19-qachGa mWntoR, 71)

src: sɯŋgɯpɤjka nɯ ɯ-mat nɯnɯ pɤjka kɯ-fse cʰɯ-βze,
trs: Wild squash grows fruits like those of the (cultivated) squash.' (16-CWrNgo, 39)

src: tɤ-pɤtso cʰo-ndzɤt
trs: The child grew up.' (elicited)

src: tʰam tɕe mɤʑɯ tɤ-dɤn-nɯ
trs: Now they are even more numerous than before.' (140522 tshupa, 86)

src: ndʑi-tɕɯ ci to-tu
trs: They had one son.' (2011-05-nyima, 2)

src: ɯ-tɕɯ to-sci ɕi, ɯ-me to-sci?
trs: Did she have a boy or a girl.' (elicited)

src: nɯʑora nɯ-ɕki ɣɯ-to-mkʰroŋ ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: He had come to be born in their (family).' (150825 nezha naohai-zh, 38)

src: tsʰɤt nɯ tʰɯ-rɤpɯ tɕe, ʁnɯz ntsɯ cʰɯ-lɤt ŋgrɤl
trs: When goats have young, they give birth to two (kids) each time.' (05-qaZo, 7)

src: tɯ-ji ɯ-ŋgɯ nɯra cʰɯ-rɤŋgɯm ŋgrɤl
trs: It lays eggs in the fields.' (24-kWmu, 85)

src: a-kɯr ɯ-ŋgɯ tɯ-ci pɯ-aʁe-a tɕe, a-sroʁ to-tu
trs: I have water in my mouth to drink, my life is back.' (2011-05-nyima, 69)

src: tɕe ɯ-rte ra ɲɤ-nɯ-βde tɕe,
trs: (The boy) lost his hat' (Pear story 2010, Tshendzin,  12)

src: mtsʰu nɯ cʰɯmcʰɯm ʑo, tɕe, tɯ-skɤm pjɤ-sɤʑa tɕe mtsʰu nɯ ɲɤ-me tɕe
trs: The level of the lake started to go down slowly and the lake disappeared.' (nyima2003, 106)

src: zgoku nɯtɕu si nɯ ʑɯrɯʑɤri ɲɯ\redp{}ɲɤ-rkɯn ʑo
trs: The trees on the mountain became fewer and fewer.' (04-xiaocunzhuang-zh, 24)

imt: sun \textsc{dem} \textsc{ipfv}:\textsc{west}-disappear \textsc{ipfv}-wait[III] be.needed:\textsc{fact} hearsay \textsc{lnk} sun \textsc{dem} really \textsc{emph} \textsc{appl}-be.afraid[III]:\textsc{fact} hearsay
src: tɤŋe nɯ ɲɯ-ɕqʰlɤt ku-nɤjɤm ra kʰi ma tɤŋe nɯ wuma ʑo nɯɣ-me kʰi.
trs: (The yeti) waits for the sun to disappear (before eating the man he has caught), because he fears the sun, it is said.' (140510 mYWrgAt, 7)

src: nɯ ma si tɤ-me tɕe li nɯ ɲɯ-pʰɯt-nɯ
trs: When there is no other wood than this, people cut it.' (07-Zmbri, 65)

src: ɯʑo ɯ-χti ɲɤ-me tɕe,
trs: Her husband passed away.' (12-BzaNsa, 127)

src: βdaʁmu nɯ to-ngo tɕe ɲɤ-si.
trs: The lady became ill and died.' (2011-05-nyima, 5)

src: jima ɯ-rɣi nɯ-plɯt-i
trs: We have used up all the maize grains.' (elicited)

src: tɕetu ʑara nɯ-ɴɢarmɯ nɯ pjɤ-si kʰi tɕe,
trs: Those up there, their cow died, it is said.' (Tagrdo conversation, 2003)

src: atu pɣɤtɕɯ nɯ ɕ-pɯ-sat-nɯ ra
trs: Go and kill the bird up there.' (2005 Kunbzang, 330)

src: tɕe nɯ-nɯŋa pjɤ-nɯ-ntɕʰa-nɯ
trs: They killed their cow (for themselves to eat).' (02-deluge2012, 17)

src: fsapaʁ ɯ-ŋgru pɯ-nɯ-ŋu, rɯdaʁ ɯ-ŋgru pɯ-nɯ-ŋu,  nɯnɯ na-ntɕʰa-nɯ tɕe tu-tɕɤt-nɯ tɕe tɕe tu-sɯɣ-rom-nɯ.
trs: Whether it is sinew$_i$ from a domestic or a wild animal,$_j$  after they butcher them,$_j$ they take it$_i$ out and dry it$_i$.' (150906 tWNgru, 6)

src: nɯnɯ pa-sat-nɯ tɕe tɕe ju-nɯ-ɣɯt-nɯ tɕe ɲɯ-ntɕʰa-nɯ
trs: After (the hunters) have killed (the animals)$_i$, they bring them$_i$ home and butcher them$_i$.' (150829 KAGWcAno, 18)

src: qartsʰi nɯ sŋi tɕe cʰɯ-nɯrɤɣo nɤ cʰɯ-nɯrɤɣo ŋu tɕe
trs: The cicada (was) singing all the time during the day. (26-NalitCaRmbWm, 30)

src: nɯnɯ rɤɣo cʰɯ-tɯ-ʑa qʰe, tɤrcɯrca ʑo cʰɯ-ti-nɯ to-cʰa-nɯ.
trs: They became able to sing along as soon as it started its song.'  (140519 yeying-zh, 162)

src: ɟuli nɯ cʰɤ-lɤt.
trs: He played the flute' (140513 mutong de disheng-zh, 85)

src: nɯnɯra kɯ rkɤdɯt cʰɯ-ʑ-mbri-nɯ pjɤ-mtsʰɤm.
trs: She heard (the hunters) blowing the horn.' (140520 ye tiane-zh, 249)

src: ɯ-lɤcu cʰɯ́-wɣ-ɣɤmɯt tɕe tɯ-rtsʰɤz nɯ ɲɯ-fka ŋu
trs: One blows (into the pig's trachea) and its lungs fill up.' (20-kAPjAt, 13)

src: ɲɯ-mɯnmu nɤ ɲɯ-mɯnmu tɕe tɕe, nɯ ɯ-ŋgɯ ɴɢoɕna kɯ-rɤʑi nɯ kɯ pjɯ-mtsʰɤm tɕe
trs: (The fly that has been caught in the spider's web) moves and moves, and the spider staying inside feels it.' (26-mYaRmtsaR, 63-64)

src: tɯmɯkɯmpɕi kɯ pɯ́-wɣ-mbi-a ŋu
trs: Heavens gave it to me.' (Norbzang 2005, 312)

src: laʁjɯɣ nɯ ɯ-taʁ nɯ ɯ-pʰe to-kʰo tɕe,
trs: He gave the staff to the (thief) who was on (the tiger).' (khu2012, 15)

src: taʁ kɯ, <piaozi> pɯ́-wɣ-mbi-j.
trs: The ones above (the government) gave us money.' (2010-09, 172)

src: nɯtɕu zɯ laftaʁ cʰɤ-tɯ-kʰo-nɯ tɕe, nɯnɯ nɯ-jɯm nɯ ɕɯ-ɕar-i ra
trs: (Since) you have given her a token, we will go and look for this (woman, your wife.' (sras 2003, 42)

src: tɕe ma nɯnɯ kumpɣa nɯnɯ, nɤkinɯ, pɯ-nɯʑɯβ tɕe ɯ-mɲaʁ ku-sɤwi ɲɯ-ŋu. tɕeri ɯ-mɲaʁ ɯ-rqʰu nɯnɯ, nɤkinɯ, pjɯ-ɣi tɕe ɯ-mɲaʁrdu nɯ pjɯ-fkaβ kɯ-fse ɲɯ-ŋu ma
trs: When the hen falls asleep, it closes its eyes. Its nictitating membrane (literally: `eye husk') comes down and covers its eyeball.' (150819 kumpGa, 52)

src: maka kʰa ntsɯ ku-kɯ-rɤʑi ku-kɯ-lkɯɣ mɯ́j-sɤ-scit.
trs: Staying at home all the time, one feels stiff, is is not nice.

src: pjɯ-kɯ-fkaβ ʑo kɯ-fse
trs: One feels like one is covered (oppressed).' (conversation, 14-05-01)

src: staχpɯ tɤ-rɲɟi tɕe stoʁ nɯ cʰɯ-fkaβ
trs: When the pea has grown, it covers the broad bean.' (25-sthoRthAB, 4)

src: kʰa ra cʰɤ-fkaβ-ndʑi
trs: They built a house.' (02-deluge2012, 131)

src: cizcʰiz ri ɲɯ-ta-nɯ tɕe tɕe, nɤki, pjɯ-fkaβ-nɯ. pjɯ-fkaβ-nɯ tɕe tɕe, ɯ-taʁ tɕe tɯ-ŋga ku-ta-nɯ, soʁma ra ku-ta-nɯ tɕe
trs: They put (the pot) somewhere and cover it. They cover it, put clothes or hay on it.' (160703 araR, 34-36)

src: ɕkɤbɯ ɯ-ŋgɯ nɯtɕu kú-wɣ-mpʰɯr ŋu.
trs: People wrap it inside onion buns.' (160706 thotsi, 43)

src: mɯrmɯmbju ɣɯ ɯ-tɯɣmaz ra to-mpʰɯr.
trs: She bound up the wound of the swallow.' (150825 huluwa-zh, 40)

src: tɕe βzɯr ri tɕe cʰɯ́-wɣ-mpʰɯr cʰɯ́-wɣ-ʑa tɕe  mɤpɕoʁ cʰu βzɯr nɯ ɯ-ɕki mɤɕtʂa cʰɯ́-wɣ-mpʰɯr.
trs: One start wrapping (the square piece of cloth) on one of the angle up until the opposite angle (on the diagonal).' (30-mboR, 20)

src: tɕe tɯ-ci ɣɯ-pjɯ-nɯ-tsʰi-nɯ
trs: (The wild yaks) come and drink water.' (20-RmbroN, 46)

src: tɕe tɯ-ci ɕ-pjɤ-nɯ-tsʰi.
trs: She went (there) and drank water.' (140428 mu e guniang-zh, 72)

src: tɕendɤre tɕetu zgo kɯ-mbɯ\redp{}mbro mɤɕtʂa to-ɕe, to-nɯrʁɯrʁa.
trs: He went up there, climbing,on the very high mountain.' (150825 huluwa-zh, 156)

src: rə-\textbf{ɕɐ}-rô-ŋ
trs: I fetched it.' (Situ)

src: qajɯ ra tu-ndze ma tɤ-rɤku ɣɯ-tu-ndze mɤ-ŋgrɤl
trs: It eats bugs, and does not come and eat the crops.' (24-ZmbrWpGa, 129) (Japhug)

src: tɕe ɯʑo nɯ ɲɤ-nɯ-pʰɣo matɕi tɕe, nɯmaʁnɤ ɣɯ́-ndza pjɤ-ŋu.
trs: (The rabbit), he fled away, otherwise he would have been eaten.' (140427 qala cho kWrtsag, 76)

src: kʰu a-jɤ-ɤzɣɯt ndɤ ɣɯ́-wɣ-ndza ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: If the tiger arrives, it (the tiger) will eat him (the man).' (kandZislama 2003, 100)

src: tɕendɤre ɯ-pɯ ra nɯ-ndza ʑ-na-ɕar
trs: The (cat mother) went to look for food for her (kitten).' (21-lWLU, 80)

src: nɯnɯ ʑakastaka kɯ-tu nɯnɯ ɣɯ nɯ-<gongfen> ra ʑ-ɲɯ-lat-a ɕ-tu-kʰat-a pɯ-ra.
trs: I had to go everywhere to count work points for every single person.' (2010-09, 79)

src: aki ɕ-pɯ-sɤŋo
trs: Go down there and listen' (many attestations).

src: pʰaʁrgot ci tu tɕe, nɯ ɕ-pɯ-sat ra
trs: There is a boar, go and kill it.' (140428 yonggan de xiaocaifeng-zh, 227-228)

src: tɕetʰa nɯ ɬɤndʐi tɤ-mu nɯnɯ ɣi tɕe nɤʑo ɣɯ-tɯ́-wɣ-nɯsnɯɲaʁ ɕti
trs: The ghost woman will come and cause you harm.' (150907 niexiaoqian-zh, 96)

src: tɕendɤre nɯnɯ ɕ-to-nɯ-ŋke-nɯ tɕe, lu χsɯ-xpa ɕ-pjɤ-ŋke-nɯ,
trs: The ministers went to look for (the girl), they walked for three years.' (sras 2003, 50)

src: kɯ-nŋo nɯ qʰe ci ci ɕ-tu-mɯrki kɯ-fse ma nɯ ma mɯ-ɲɯ-ɤʁe.
trs: The (lion) which is defeated steals a little out of it, but apart from that has nothing to eat.' (20-sWNgi, 65)

src: rɟa ɣɯ ɯ-laχtɕʰa tu-ɣɯt-a tɕe pot zɯ ɕ-tu-ntsɣe-a, pot ɣɯ ɯ-laχtɕʰa pjɯ-ɣɯt-a tɕe, rɟa zɯ ɕ-pjɯ-ntsɣe-a.
trs: I bring things (down) from central Tibet, and sell them in China.' (28-qAjdoskAt, 15-16)

src: lo-mɯrkɯ pjɤ-cʰa tɕe lo-ɣɯt ri
trs: He was able to steal it and brought it upstream.' (02-montagnes-kamnyu-cz, 31)

src: tɕi-kɯm lu-pe-a je!
trs: Let me close the door (for us).' (conversation, 03-05-2018, Tshendzin)

src: tɕe mbroχpa ri jla nɯ s-cʰɯ-χtɯ-nɯ ʁɟa pɯ-ra.
trs: People had to buy hybrid yaks from the nomads.' (150820 kAnWCkat, 26)

src: atʰi ɯ-pɕi ri <chengdu> ri <diannao> ci ɕ-pa-βzjoz
trs: He went outside of (Tibetan areas, downstream), to Chengdu, and learnt computers there a little bit.' (12-BzaNsa, 82)

src: pʰɤri praʁ ɯ-ŋgɯ mɤɕtʂa ku-tsɯm qʰe, tɕe nɯtɕu ɕ-tu-ndze ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: (The eagle) takes (the young animal) to the cliff on the other side (of the river) and eats it there.' (19-qandZGi, 51)

src: tɕe ɯ-zrɤm ju-ɕe qʰe nɯre ri, kɯmaʁ ɯ-pɕoʁ ɕ-tu-ɬoʁ ɲɯ-ɕti ma
trs: Its root moves and it grows there, at a different place.' (15-babW, 46)

src: a-nɯ-χɕaʁ, a-nɯ-si tɕe tɕe, kɯmaʁ pɕoʁ ri li ɕ-tu-sci ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: When (the reincarnated lama) passes away, he is born in another place.' (160722 skWBli, 2)

src: tɕe saɕɯ nɯ tɯrgi ɯ-locu zɯ ɕ-to-ɬoʁ tɕe, tɕe nɯnɯ tɤ-ftsa nɯ tɤ-rpɯ sɤz lu-kɯ-maŋlo mɯ-pjɤ-ŋgrɤl
trs: The larch grew on a place higher than the fir, but nephews could not be seated higher (upstream) than their maternal uncles (and this is why the larch became deciduous).' (08-saCW)

src: <guanzi> ɯ-ŋgɯ ri ɕ-tɤ-rɯndzɤtsʰi-j.
trs: We went to a restaurant and ate there.' (2010-1, 13)

src: tɯrme kɯ-xtɕi nɯnɯra sɲikuku ʑo sɯŋgɯ ju-ɕe-nɯ tɕe, iɕqʰa nɯ, tsʰitsuku z-ɲɯ-ɕar-nɯ pjɤ-ŋu tɕe, χsɤr ra ɕ-tu-βzdɯ-nɯ pjɤ-ŋu.
trs: The dwarfs went everyday into the forest, searched around and collected gold there. ' (140504 baixuegongzhu-zh, 98-99)

src: jaʁmɤzdoʁzdoʁ nɯ kɯ qajɯ ra tu-ndze ma tɤ-rɤku ɣɯ-tu-ndze mɤ-ŋgrɤl
trs: The bird \forme{jaʁmɤzdoʁzdoʁ} eats bugs, it does not come and eat crops.' (24-ZmbrWpGa, 131)

src: ji-me nɯ kɯ βɣɯz ʁnɯz ʑo ɕ-pjɤ-sat.
trs: Our daughter-in-law went (to look for badgers) and killed two badgers.' (27-spjaNkW, 111)

src: zgoku tɤ-ari nɤ, `hehe a-ʑi ra cʰɤ-tɯ-nɯ-rɤrɟit-nɯ mɯ́j-tɯ-nɯ-sɯχsɤl-nɯ' ɕ-ta-tɯt ɲɯ-ŋu
trs: He went up the mountain top and said: `My lady, you had a child and did not notice it.' (2003 Kunbzang, 118)

src: tɕʰi ɯ-taʁ to-ɕe tɕe ɕ-tɤ-ru
trs: He went up the stairs and looked up.'  (08-kWqhi, 18)

imt: house \textsc{neg}-\textsc{pst}.\textsc{ipfv}-stay \textsc{lnk} \textsc{lnk} summer \textsc{dem} really \textsc{emph} badger \textsc{ifr}.\textsc{ipfv}-cause.damage \textsc{lnk} completely threshold \textsc{pl} also \textsc{ipfv}-come \textsc{cisl}-\textsc{ipfv}-dig.up \textsc{ifr}.\textsc{ipfv}-be
src: kʰa mɯ-pɯ-rɤʑi tɕe tɕe, ftɕar nɯ wuma ʑo βɣɯz pjɤ-rɯŋɯŋɤn tɕe maka, kɯmtʰoʁ ra kɯnɤ ju-ɣi ɣɯ-ɲɯ-sloʁ pjɤ-ŋu.
trs: He was not at home, and badgers were causing a lot of damage that summer, they came and even dug up the threshold of the house.'  (27-spjaNkW, 107)

src: tɤ-tɕɯ nɯ to-ɕe tɕe ɕ-pjɤ-ru ri,
trs: The boy went up and looked down.' (2012 Norbzang, 57)

src: ci ci ɯ-mi kɯ iɕqʰa, lɯlu ɣɯ ɯ-mi nɯra z-ɲɯ-z-nɤtsʰɣɤz. kɯra ɕ-tu-ste tɕe ɕ-ku-nɯrtɕe ra pjɤ-ŋu.
trs: (The mouse) sometimes went and touched the cat's legs with its leg, it (went and) teased (the cat) like that.' (150902 dashu-zh, 31)

src: ɯ-loʁ ɯ-ŋgɯ ri z-ju-sɯ-mtsʰɤt ʑo z-ju-ski
trs: (The mole)$_i$ goes to its nest$_j$ and buries (so much of the food$_k$ it$_i$ has collected that it$_i$) fills it$_j$ up.' (28-qapar, 172)

src: pɯ-ari ndɤre jɯɣi nɯ ɕ-ta-ru ɲɯ-ŋu.
trs: He went down (to the bottom of the ocean) and brought up the sutra.' (2005 Norbzang, 236)

src: kɯki sɤlaŋpʰɤn ki nɤʑo ŋotɕu z-jɤ-tɯ-ru-t ŋu?
trs: Where did you get this washbasin from?' (150831 jubaopen-zh, 138)

src: atu tɤ-mtʰɯm ɕ-pɯ-re
trs: Bring (down) the meat from up there.' (meimeidegushi, 204)

src: sɤcɯ z-ɲɯ-re-a
trs: I will fetch the key (over there, towards east).' (heard in context, 2014)

src: tha qaliaʁ nɯ kɯ a-rɟit ɣɯ-nɯ-re
trs: The eagle will come and take my child away.' (140427 laoying mao he yezhu-zh, 47)

src: kutɕu ʑo rdɤstaʁ ɣɯ-ɲɯ-ru-ndʑi iʑora ɣɯ ra mɤ-ŋgrɤl ɯ-maʁ ma
trs: They come here to take stones away, as if we did not need them.' (conversation, 14-05-10)

src: tɕekɯ taʁrdo ra kɤ-ɣe-ndʑi
trs: They came to Tagrdo (and looked for stones).' (conversation, 14-05-10)

src: tɕʰeme nɯ kɯ popo to-ndo tɕe, tɯ-ci ʑ-lo-ru ri,
trs: The woman took an earthenware and brought water.' (Gesar, 328)

src: ʑ-lo-ru ri ci ra mɯ-lo-ɕqʰlɤt-nɯ
trs: He went there and had a look up there, but the other ones had not (yet) disappeared.' (tWJo 2005, 74)

src: tɕendɤre [tɯ-ci ɕɯ-kɤ-ru] nɯ-ʁjiz kɯ-ɣi maka ʑo pjɤ-me
trs: None of them wanted to fetch water (anymore).' (150830 san ge heshang-zh, 137)

src: [kɯki χsɤr pɣɤtɕɯ ki ɕɯ-kɯ-ru] ɕɯ pɯ-kɯ-cha nɯ a-sci rɟɤlpu cʰɯ-ta-sɯ-ndo-nɯ ŋu
trs: Whoever among you succeeds in finding and bringing this golden bird here, I will give him the throne.' (qachGa2012, 24)
